The rare disease that a man suffers from
Nick Hess was an American banished by his family as an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was in a daze, he could barely stand and his words were hard to understand.
Although the 35-year-old man said he had not consumed alcohol, he was clearly in a state of intoxication.
When she first accused me of being drunk, without having been drunk, I thought she was crazy.
"But friends and family thought 'maybe he drinks alone, he's a secret alcoholic'", he says, according to the Mirror.
When he saw the footage of his wife with him, the man from Columbus, Ohio, simply didn't recognize himself: "I was looking into my own eyes and I wasn't there".
'It was horrible, I couldn't remember anything.'
In addition, his wife, who, though she had doubted him for a while, eventually went with him to countless doctors, remembers that Nick's breath smelled like alcohol.
The most sobering moment for Nick was when, after a minor car accident, he was found to have a blood alcohol level three times the legal limit, even though the night before he had only had one beer.
After years and countless investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffered from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndrome".
Basically, his body is fermenting all the carbohydrates he consumes, turning them into alcohol.
The one who suspected that this might be Nick's disease was his own wife.
The disease has no cure yet, but since he gave up carbohydrates, Nick has had no such episodes.
