What do we do with these people?
My prediction is that we'll get used to this problem, we'll stop looking at it as catastrophic from a media point of view.
Talk about countries with more or less experience.
Do you think there's any place that has really succeeded in integrating large groups from a non-European culture?
I look at the Maghreb in France, the Turks in Germany, they're still enclaved.
I wouldn't go as far as to make a radical statement.
Of course, their integration is more difficult than other waves of migration, but that doesn't mean they don't integrate at all.
There's an unintegrated part that creates major social problems in France, in Germany, in Britain.
