To create a fortified Europe is illusory.
We must work on the mechanisms of integration into European societies.
There's been some mistakes.
We have to be more demanding.
We ask these people to learn the language, to try to take over the values, to no longer stay with one foot in Europe and one in their country of origin, bringing the rest of their family including through marriages of convenience.
But we have to separate the imminent problem of these people from the long-term problem of their integration.
Just because others have failed to integrate long-term doesn't mean we have to watch them drown in the Mediterranean.
Maybe we're doubting the quality of the values these people come with.
